Software stored in Firmware and Proprietary USB Cable & Connector
I pre-ordered this drive months before it was available because I thought it would be just like the traditional WD My Passport drives that I have recommended to so many people. I use these drives on my Mac systems and I now no longer recommend the WD My Passport series to anyone. Instead, I strongly recommend against them. First, I generally do not like the software that is included with external hard drives. Whenever I buy a new drive I immediately format it to get rid of any of the extra software. When I first plugged this drive in, I discovered an additional volume was loaded that contains the software. I thought maybe this was like some other drives I had used that want you to format the rest of the drive to match your system or something like that. I tried formatting and whatever method I could think of to get rid of that extra volume. A quick search revealed that this volume is built into the firmware and is always there whether you like it or not. I DO NOT like being forced to have an extra volume around. This software problem was bad but on top of that, WD had to use a tiny little USB connector that I have never seen before which is totally incompatible with all of my mini USB cables. To make it even worse, this connector is so loose and flimsy that if I move the cable the slightest bit, it falls out. This is not acceptable for a portable hard drive. Western Digital is going the wrong way! Avoid their external portable drives like the plague!! Please bring back the older style drives that used normal mini USB cables and did not have any software that you cannot get rid of!!
      
