Proceed with Caution
I purchased this item from Amazon ($147).  From my experience the manufacturer has poor quality control.  <br />1) The box was missing a part (the wand). <br />2) The foot peddle is poorly designed and seems prone to damage<br />3) The belt fails to disengage when in the upright position; this caused the belt to slowly burn out.  This may be the cause of the belt problems others are complaining about.  This issue may be isolated to my machine, however, the poor foot peddle design makes me wonder if this product was fully thought out in the design stage.<br /><br />On the bright side, Amazon arranged for a UPS pick up at my home and provided a refund.  I'm happy with the Hoover UH50000 (Amazon $199) that I ordered in its place. <br />
      
