Falls apart after a few months
I bought the Eureka 4870MZ Boss Smart-vac 3/19/09. It is now 7/25/09, and the vacuum is already falling apart. The vacuum was an okay one, but I accepted it's shortcomings, because it was cheap enough. It vacuums pretty well across several different floor surfaces (carpet, tile, laminate), but it was heavy, generated a lot of heat, attachments would fall off all the time, and switching between bare floors and carpet and between hose and floor was unnecessarily cumbersome. As I said I was willing to live with this, because of the price. My previous vacuum had been a $400 Dyson which was a nightmare, and I vowed never to spend that much on a vacuum again. But now, here I am, just over four months later, and the Eureka is no longer usuable. First, the cheap plastic wheels are falling off. Second, the switch that you turn to change from floor to hose no longer works properly, so that now I can't use anything but the hose. Basically what I have now is a really expensive Dust Buster. My floors are filthy and I can't vacuum. Other reviews have made reference to the cheap quality of this vacuum, and it falling apart after a few months. I should've listened. If you value your money, I would not recommend this vacuum.
      
