PRODUCT HAS DEFECTS - SHOULD BE RECALLED
Our company bought 8 HD 202 headsets in Sept 2008. After 3 months of use four of the headsets quit working at a rate of one per week. The company is good at honoring replacements but one must pay for the shipment there. If you buy these through Amazon the company will NOT refund the purchase price no matter what. They will just continue sending replacements. For us that means A LOT of down time as we have to wait for the replaced headsets to be shipped back. The problem with all of the headsets is that one side abruptly quits working. It appears to be a defect in the product and probably should be recalled (in my opinion). <br /><br />So...purchase at your own risk. You might not be using them after the one year warranty is up.
      
