<!-- BOUNDARY -->
It's in the trash now
Having just removed my unit and thrown it in the trash, I would like to say that I respectfully disagree with the reviewer who wrote the "most helpful" earlier review. <br /><br />1. The fact that it is a "name brand" is meaningless. Some other company arranged for a license to use the famous Schwinn name. That says nothing about product quality.<br /><br />2. Many of the functions are completely pointless padding, useful only as a marketing gimmick. Such things as calorie count and fat burning make no sense without details about terrain and other conditions. I once coasted down Mt. Haleakala in Maui. Hours of biking; zero calories! There are very sophisticated (and expensive) bike computers that measure pedal rotation and elevation. This is not one of them, and should not pretend to be.<br /><br />3. The installation instructions are not only hard to understand; they are dead wrong. They refer to mounting clamps that don't exist; the unit now relies on plastic cable ties instead.<br /><br />4. Mostly what I want - and I suspect almost everyone wants - from a bike computer is easy display of speed and distance. This unit cannot be set to always show those two vital statistics full-time by default.<br /><br />5. Controlling functions requires arbitrary pushing and holding of one or the other buttons, in combinations that make no logical sense. Changing functions while riding may be dangerous to the rider.<br /><br />6. Despite the earlier reviewer's belief that we should "feel foolish" for not reading the instructions to his satisfaction, the ones who should feel foolish are those who designed the human interface for this monstrosity. A simple device shouldn't require careful study of a user manual, especially one written in 6-point type.<br /><br />I really tried to give this unit every chance, and as a result went beyond Amazon's 30-day return window. So, a ten-buck lesson that I hope others will benefit from. I just bought and installed the Planet Bike Protégé 9.0 9-Function Bike Computer, also on Amazon, and it is terrific. Three times the price, but well worth it in my opinion.
      
