A Frustrating Waste of Money
This product has terrible drivers that constantly malfunction. The one big feature of this scanner- the automatic photo feeder, never works. It just tries to pull a picture in but fails (no matter how many you put in the feeder, what size they are, how far you stuff them in), then scans a blank page, saves it, and continues to do this over and over indefinitely until you either run out of hard drive space or remove the pictures from the feeder. In the rare event it tries to suck anything through, it either scratches up the print, or else tries to suck through ten prints at once and gets jammed and mangles them. In the extremely rare event that I ever get it to scan a picture, there's no auto cropping for the sheet feeder, so every picture has a lot of scanner-background that has to be manually cropped out of every image. HP has great auto-cropping software that comes with their OfficeJet line of scanners, but they don't have it for their sheet feed scanners, where it really matters. <br /><br />Additionally, while it comes with a slide and negative adapter, the dynamic range is pitiful- this scanner can't even get saturated blacks off a print- so the slide and negative scanning is near worthless. <br /><br />Please save your money and buy something else- this product is terrible.
      
